name: Beacon of Immortality

name: Honor Guard
text: {W}: Honor Guard gets +0/+1 until end of turn.

name: Reviving Dose
text: You gain 3 life.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Samite healers never mix their pungent elixir with sweetener or tea. The threat of a second dose is enough to get most warriors back on their feet.

name: Reya Dawnbringer

name: Righteousness

name: Serra Angel

name: Serra's Embrace

name: Skyhunter Patrol

name: Skyhunter Skirmisher
text: Flying, double strike
flavor: "Take the deadly grace and strength of the leonin, combined with a pteron mount capable of rending a foe in two and armed with notched steel. That is a skyhunter-�and why Taj-Nar has never fallen."\n-�Raksha Golden Cub

name: Soul Warden
text: Whenever another creature enters the battlefield, you gain 1 life.
flavor: Count carefully the souls and see that none are lost.\n-�Vec teaching

text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nWhenever enchanted creature deals damage, you gain that much life.

name: Spirit Weaver

flavor: "Let my hope be your shield."

name: Starlight Invoker
text: {7}{W}: You gain 5 life.
flavor: "The constellations form a tapestry of light that traces my people's broken history. Day and night, I feel their glittering presence calling me to weave the pattern whole."

name: Steadfast Guard

flavor: "Best leave your tongue in its yap-hole, Mercadian scum, for your silvered words and golden bribes do not sparkle so brightly outside your city."

name: Story Circle

name: Suntail Hawk
text: Flying

name: True Believer

name: Tundra Wolves
text: First strike (This creature deals combat damage before creatures without first strike.)

name: Venerable Monk
text: When Venerable Monk enters the battlefield, you gain 2 life.

name: Voice of All
text: Flying\nAs Voice of All enters the battlefield, choose a color.\nVoice of All has protection from the chosen color.

name: Wild Griffin
text: Flying

name: Wrath of God

name: Youthful Knight

name: Peek

name: Persuasion

name: Puppeteer

name: Remove Soul

name: Rootwater Commando
text: Islandwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls an Island.)

name: Rootwater Matriarch

name: Sage Owl
text: Flying\nWhen Sage Owl enters the battlefield, look at the top four cards of your library, then put them back in any order.

name: Scalpelexis

name: Sea Monster
text: Sea Monster can't attack unless defending player controls an Island.
flavor: It's easy to believe the monster is a myth-�until you feel three hundred thousand pounds of myth crashing down on your ship.

text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature has flying. (It can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{U}: Return Shimmering Wings to its owner's hand.

text: Draw three cards, then discard a card.

name: Sky Weaver
text: {2}: Target white or black creature gains flying until end of turn. (It can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)
flavor: "Let my wisdom give you wings."

name: Snapping Drake
text: Flying

name: Spiketail Hatchling
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nSacrifice Spiketail Hatchling: Counter target spell unless its controller pays {1}.

name: Sunken Hope
text: At the beginning of each player's upkeep, that player returns a creature he or she controls to its owner's hand.

name: Telepathy
text: Your opponents play with their hands revealed.
flavor: "The question isn't whether I can read minds. It's whether I have yet to find a mind worth reading."\n-�Ambassador Laquatus

name: Telling Time
text: Look at the top three cards of your library. Put one of those cards into your hand, one on top of your library, and one on the bottom of your library.

name: Tidings

name: Twincast
text: Copy target instant or sorcery spell. You may choose new targets for the copy.
flavor: Imitation is the most dangerous form of flattery.

name: Twitch
text: You may tap or untap target artifact, creature, or land.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Battles are won in nuance.

name: Unsummon
text: Return target creature to its owner's hand.
flavor: Tolarian apprentices learn to liberate Ætheric energy long before they are taught to bind it.

name: Vedalken Mastermind
text: {U}, {T}: Return target permanent you control to its owner's hand.

name: Wall of Air

name: Afflict
text: Target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.\nDraw a card.

name: Ascendant Evincar

flavor: His soul snared by an angel's curse, Crovax twisted heroism into its purest shadow.

name: Assassinate
text: Destroy target tapped creature.
flavor: "This is how wars are won-�not with armies of soldiers but with a single knife blade, artfully placed."\n-�Yurin, royal assassin

name: Beacon of Unrest
text: Put target artifact or creature card from a graveyard onto the battlefield under your control. Shuffle Beacon of Unrest into its owner's library.

text: Spend only black mana on X.\nConsume Spirit deals X damage to target creature or player and you gain X life.

name: Contaminated Bond

name: Cruel Edict

flavor: "Choose your next words carefully. They will be your last."\n-�Phage the Untouchable

name: Deathmark
text: Destroy target green or white creature.
flavor: "I hope it's true that every snowflake is unique, because I never want to see one like this again. Now clean up that body."\n-�Thangbrand Gyrdsson, Kjeldoran patrol

name: Diabolic Tutor
text: Search your library for a card and put that card into your hand. Then shuffle your library.
flavor: The best ideas often come from the worst minds.

name: Distress
text: Target player reveals his or her hand. You choose a nonland card from it. That player discards that card.
flavor: "They say the eyes are the windows to the soul. I like to break windows and take what's inside."\n-�Braids, dementia summoner

name: Doomed Necromancer
text: {B}, {T}, Sacrifice Doomed Necromancer: Return target creature card from your graveyard to the battlefield.
flavor: Many necromancers share the same last words-�the ones that conclude the undeath ritual.

name: Dross Crocodile

name: Dusk Imp
text: Flying

text: When Festering Goblin dies, target creature gets -1/-1 until end of turn.

text: Target opponent puts the cards from his or her hand on top of his or her library. Search that player's library for that many cards. The player puts those cards into his or her hand, then shuffles his or her library.

name: Hidden Horror

name: Knight of Dusk
text: {B}{B}: Destroy target creature blocking Knight of Dusk.

name: Looming Shade

flavor: "Do not weep at your defeat, my dear. In death, you will serve a greater purpose-�mine."

name: Mass of Ghouls

name: Megrim

name: Mortivore

name: Nantuko Husk
text: Sacrifice a creature: Nantuko Husk gets +2/+2 until end of turn.

name: Nekrataal
text: First strike\nWhen Nekrataal enters the battlefield, destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. That creature can't be regenerated.
flavor: His victims don't have time to feel despair.

name: Nightmare
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nNightmare's power and toughness are each equal to the number of Swamps you control.
flavor: The thunder of its hooves beats dreams into despair.

name: No Rest for the Wicked
text: Sacrifice No Rest for the Wicked: Return to your hand all creature cards in your graveyard that were put there from the battlefield this turn.
flavor: "The soul? Here, we have no use for such frivolities."\n-�Sitrik, birth priest

name: Phage the Untouchable
text: When Phage the Untouchable enters the battlefield, if you didn't cast it from your hand, you lose the game.\nWhenever Phage deals combat damage to a creature, destroy that creature. It can't be regenerated.\nWhenever Phage deals combat damage to a player, that player loses the game.

name: Phyrexian Rager
text: When Phyrexian Rager enters the battlefield, you draw a card and you lose 1 life.
flavor: It takes no prisoners, but it keeps the choicest bits for Phyrexia.

name: Plague Beetle
text: Swampwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Swamp.)
flavor: No one knows whether they were named for the disease they carry or for the speed at which they multiply.

name: Plague Wind

name: Rain of Tears

name: Ravenous Rats
text: When Ravenous Rats enters the battlefield, target opponent discards a card.
flavor: Nothing is sacred to rats. Everything is simply another meal.

name: Recover
text: Return target creature card from your graveyard to your hand.\nDraw a card.

name: Relentless Rats
text: Relentless Rats gets +1/+1 for each other creature on the battlefield named Relentless Rats.\nA deck can have any number of cards named Relentless Rats.

name: Royal Assassin
text: {T}: Destroy target tapped creature.
flavor: Trained in the arts of stealth, royal assassins choose their victims carefully, relying on timing and precision rather than brute force.

name: Scathe Zombies
flavor:
"They groaned, they stirred, they all uprose,
Nor spake, nor moved their eyes;
It had been strange, even in a dream,
To have seen those dead men rise."
-�Samuel Taylor Coleridge,
"The Rime of the Ancient Mariner"

name: Sengir Vampire
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\nWhenever a creature dealt damage by Sengir Vampire this turn dies, put a +1/+1 counter on Sengir Vampire.
flavor: Empires rise and fall, but evil is eternal.

name: Severed Legion
text: Fear (This creature can't be blocked except by artifact creatures and/or black creatures.)
flavor: No one in Aphetto answers a knock at the door after sundown.

name: Sleeper Agent
text: When Sleeper Agent enters the battlefield, target opponent gains control of it.\nAt the beginning of your upkeep, Sleeper Agent deals 2 damage to you.

name: Soul Feast
text: Target player loses 4 life and you gain 4 life.
flavor: "I smell the tang of a mortal's fresh blood. I hear it sliding wetly beneath its skin. My hunger cannot refuse the invitation."\n-�Yuri, Sengir vampire

name: Spineless Thug
text: Spineless Thug can't block.
flavor: What it lacks in backbone, it makes up for in cruelty.

name: Stronghold Discipline
text: Each player loses 1 life for each creature he or she controls.
flavor: In Urborg, the instigators of each new rebellion are soaked in the blood of the last.

name: Terror
text: Destroy target nonartifact, nonblack creature. It can't be regenerated.

name: Thrull Surgeon
text: {1}{B}, Sacrifice Thrull Surgeon: Look at target player's hand and choose a card from it. That player discards that card. Activate this ability only any time you could cast a sorcery.
flavor: "Just take a little off the top."

name: Underworld Dreams
text: Whenever an opponent draws a card, Underworld Dreams deals 1 damage to him or her.

name: Unholy Strength
text: Enchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+1.
flavor: Such power grows the body as it shrinks the soul.

name: Vampire Bats
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{B}: Vampire Bats gets +1/+0 until end of turn. Activate this ability no more than twice each turn.

name: Anaba Bodyguard
text: First strike (This creature deals combat damage before creatures without first strike.)
flavor: "They who challenge a minotaur enjoy the taste of their own blood."\n-�Mirri of the Weatherlight

name: Arcane Teachings
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and has "{T}: This creature deals 1 damage to target creature or player."

name: Beacon of Destruction

name: Blaze
text: Blaze deals X damage to target creature or player.

name: Bloodrock Cyclops
text: Bloodrock Cyclops attacks each turn if able.

name: Bogardan Firefiend
text: When Bogardan Firefiend dies, it deals 2 damage to target creature.

name: Demolish

name: Firebreathing
text: Enchant creature\n{R}: Enchanted creature gets +1/+0 until end of turn.

name: Fists of the Anvil

name: Flamewave Invoker

name: Flowstone Slide

name: Goblin Piker

name: Goblin Sky Raider
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)

name: Guerrilla Tactics
text: Guerrilla Tactics deals 2 damage to target creature or player.\nWhen a spell or ability an opponent controls causes you to discard Guerrilla Tactics, Guerrilla Tactics deals 4 damage to target creature or player.

name: Hill Giant

name: Incinerate
text: Incinerate deals 3 damage to target creature or player. A creature dealt damage this way can't be regenerated this turn.

name: Kamahl, Pit Fighter
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\n{T}: Kamahl, Pit Fighter deals 3 damage to target creature or player.

name: Lava Axe
text: Lava Axe deals 5 damage to target player.

name: Lavaborn Muse

name: Lightning Elemental
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)

name: Manabarbs
text: Whenever a player taps a land for mana, Manabarbs deals 1 damage to that player.
flavor: "I don't know why people say a double-edged sword is bad. It's a sword. With two edges."\n-�Kamahl, pit fighter

name: Mogg Fanatic
text: Sacrifice Mogg Fanatic: Mogg Fanatic deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "I got it! I got it! I-�"

name: Orcish Artillery
text: {T}: Orcish Artillery deals 2 damage to target creature or player and 3 damage to you.
flavor: "So they want to kill my men? Well two can play at that game."\n-�General Khurzog

name: Prodigal Pyromancer
text: {T}: Prodigal Pyromancer deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: "What am I looking at? Ashes, dead man."

name: Pyroclasm
text: Pyroclasm deals 2 damage to each creature.
flavor: "When the air burns, only death breathes deep."\n-�Bogardan mage

name: Rage Weaver
text: {2}: Target black or green creature gains haste until end of turn. (It can attack and {T} this turn.)
flavor: "Let my passion spur your victory."

name: Raging Goblin
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: He raged at the world, at his family, at his life. But mostly he just raged.

name: Relentless Assault
text: Untap all creatures that attacked this turn. After this main phase, there is an additional combat phase followed by an additional main phase.
flavor: "Mercy? Mercy is for the playground, not the battleground."

name: Rock Badger
text: Mountainwalk (This creature can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Mountain.)
flavor: "As it charged our keep, I mistook it for a bear. After it tore through our ramparts and half the guard, I wished it had been a bear after all."\n-�Ballista guard

name: Seismic Assault
text: Discard a land card: Seismic Assault deals 2 damage to target creature or player.

text: Destroy all artifacts. They can't be regenerated.

name: Shivan Hellkite
text: Flying (This creature can't be blocked except by creatures with flying or reach.)\n{1}{R}: Shivan Hellkite deals 1 damage to target creature or player.
flavor: A dragon's scale can be carved into a mighty shield, provided you can procure a dragontooth to cut it.

name: Shock
text: Shock deals 2 damage to target creature or player.

name: Shunt

flavor: Aranghil held her fury in her heart, hard and bright as a ruby. With its razor edge, she rewrote the laws of battle.

name: Siege-Gang Commander
text: When Siege-Gang Commander enters the battlefield, put three 1/1 red Goblin creature tokens onto the battlefield.\n{1}{R}, Sacrifice a Goblin: Siege-Gang Commander deals 2 damage to target creature or player.

name: Smash
text: Destroy target artifact.\nDraw a card.
flavor: Ravnica's laws protect not its citizens but its industry. Aging equipment is destroyed rather than restored, to bring more money into the factories' coffers.

name: Soulblast
text: As an additional cost to cast Soulblast, sacrifice all creatures you control.\nSoulblast deals damage to target creature or player equal to the total power of the sacrificed creatures.

name: Spark Elemental
text: Trample, haste (If this creature would assign enough damage to its blockers to destroy them, you may have it assign the rest of its damage to defending player or planeswalker. This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\nAt the beginning of the end step, sacrifice Spark Elemental.
flavor: Vulshok shamans could never keep them alive for more than a few seconds, yet those few seconds seemed to be enough.

name: Spitting Earth
text: Spitting Earth deals damage to target creature equal to the number of Mountains you control.
flavor: "Within each of you is the strength of a landslide."\n-�Kumano, to his pupils

name: Squee, Goblin Nabob
text: At the beginning of your upkeep, you may return Squee, Goblin Nabob from your graveyard to your hand.
flavor: "Some goblins are expendable. Some are impossible to get rid of. But he's both-�at the same time!"\n-�Starke

name: Stun
text: Target creature can't block this turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: "Fortunately, merfolk aren't used to opponents with feet."\n-�Gerrard of the Weatherlight

name: Sudden Impact
text: Sudden Impact deals damage to target player equal to the number of cards in that player's hand.
flavor: "Some say it's better to think before you act. While those people are considering all the options, that's usually when I kill them."\n-�Dravus, lava mage

name: Threaten
text: Untap target creature and gain control of it until end of turn. That creature gains haste until end of turn. (It can attack and {T} this turn.)
flavor: Goblins' motivational techniques are crude, but effective.

name: Thundering Giant
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)
flavor: The giant was felt a few seconds before he was seen.

name: Uncontrollable Anger
text: Flash (You may cast this spell any time you could cast an instant.)\nEnchant creature\nEnchanted creature gets +2/+2 and attacks each turn if able.
flavor: A barbarian's heart pounds with the fury of a prisoner, threatening at any moment to break the bars of its cage.

name: Viashino Runner
text: Menace (This creature can't be blocked except by two or more creatures.)
flavor: "It moved this way, an' that way, an' then before I could stick it, it jumped over my head an' was gone."\n-�Jula, goblin raider

name: Viashino Sandscout
text: Haste (This creature can attack and {T} as soon as it comes under your control.)\nAt the beginning of the end step, return Viashino Sandscout to its owner's hand. (Return it only if it's on the battlefield.)
flavor: A viashino's overlapping scales form a buffer against Shiv's ash-flecked winds and a slippery target for goblin pikes.

name: Wall of Fire
text: Defender (This creature can't attack.)\n{R}: Wall of Fire gets +1/+0 until end of turn.
flavor: The erupting flames work as both barrier and weapon.

name: Warp World
text: Each player shuffles all permanents he or she owns into his or her library, then reveals that many cards from the top of his or her library. Each player puts all artifact, creature, and land cards revealed this way onto the battlefield, then does the same for enchantment cards, then puts all cards revealed this way that weren't put onto the battlefield on the bottom of his or her library.

name: Abundance
text: If you would draw a card, you may instead choose land or nonland and reveal cards from the top of your library until you reveal a card of the chosen kind. Put that card into your hand and put all other cards revealed this way on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Aggressive Urge
text: Target creature gets +1/+1 until end of turn.\nDraw a card.
flavor: The power of the wild, concentrated in a single charge.

name: Avatar of Might
text: If an opponent controls at least four more creatures than you, Avatar of Might costs {6} less to cast.\nTrample (This creature can deal excess combat damage to defending player or planeswalker while attacking.)
flavor: In their most desperate hour, the elves of Llanowar had one song left to sing.

name: Birds of Paradise
text: Flying\n{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool.

name: Blanchwood Armor
text: Enchant creature (Target a creature as you cast this. This card enters the battlefield attached to that creature.)\nEnchanted creature gets +1/+1 for each Forest you control.
flavor: "Before armor, there was bark. Before blades, there were thorns."\n-�Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Canopy Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: It keeps the upper reaches of the forest free of every menace . . . except for the spider itself.

name: Civic Wayfinder
text: When Civic Wayfinder enters the battlefield, you may search your library for a basic land card, reveal it, and put it into your hand. If you do, shuffle your library.
flavor: "These alleys are not safe. Come, I can guide you back to the market square."

name: Commune with Nature
text: Look at the top five cards of your library. You may reveal a creature card from among them and put it into your hand. Put the rest on the bottom of your library in any order.

name: Craw Wurm
flavor: The most terrifying thing about the craw wurm is probably the horrible crashing sound it makes as it speeds through the forest. This noise is so loud it echoes through the trees and seems to come from all directions at once.

name: Creeping Mold
text: Destroy target artifact, enchantment, or land.
flavor: Mold crept over the walls and into every crevice until the gleaming white stone strained and burst.

name: Elven Riders
text: Elven Riders can't be blocked except by Walls and/or creatures with flying.
flavor: "Wirewood cannot hide great size. Only with speed and skill can we survive here."

name: Elvish Berserker
text: Whenever Elvish Berserker becomes blocked, it gets +1/+1 until end of turn for each creature blocking it.
flavor: Their fury scatters enemies like a pile of dry leaves.

name: Elvish Champion
text: Other Elf creatures get +1/+1 and have forestwalk. (They can't be blocked as long as defending player controls a Forest.)
flavor: "For what are leaves but countless blades\nTo fight a countless foe on high."\n-�Elvish hymn

name: Elvish Piper
text: {G}, {T}: You may put a creature card from your hand onto the battlefield.
flavor: From Gaea grew the world, and the world was silent. From Gaea grew the world's elves, and the world was silent no more.\n-�Elvish teaching

name: Enormous Baloth
flavor: Its diet consists of fruits, plants, small woodland animals, large woodland animals, woodlands, fruit groves, fruit farmers, and small cities.

name: Femeref Archers
text: {T}: Femeref Archers deals 4 damage to target attacking creature with flying.
flavor: "Bet you can't put it through the eye."\n"Left or right?"

name: Gaea's Herald
text: Creature spells can't be countered.
flavor: "Gaea sings with the voice of nature rampant: a thousand howls, chitters, and cries, and none of them can be ignored."

name: Giant Growth
text: Target creature gets +3/+3 until end of turn.

name: Giant Spider
text: Reach (This creature can block creatures with flying.)
flavor: "When I trained under Multani, he bade me sit for hours watching Yavimaya's spiders. From them I learned stealth, patience, and the best way to snare a wind drake."\n-�Mirri of the Weatherlight

name: Grizzly Bears
flavor: "We cannot forget that among all of Dominaria's wonders, a system of life exists, with prey and predators that will never fight wars nor vie for ancient power."\n-�Jolrael, empress of beasts

name: Hunted Wumpus
text: When Hunted Wumpus enters the battlefield, each other player may put a creature card from his or her hand onto the battlefield.
flavor: Just one can feed a dozen people for a month.

name: Hurricane
text: Hurricane deals X damage to each creature with flying and each player.
flavor: "Don't envy the grandeur of drakes. Their impression of grace fades when the first gust sends them crashing into one another."\n-�Molimo, maro-sorcerer

name: Joiner Adept
text: Lands you control have "{T}: Add one mana of any color to your mana pool."
flavor: A talented apprentice makes all things. The master makes all things possible.

name: Karplusan Strider
